The paper deals with the identification of devices based on their communication patterns, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of deep learning techniques such as Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the use of network infrastructure and communication protocols, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The use of image processing techniques to analyze the graphs of Inter Arrival Time (IAT) suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV). Finally, the paper involves the use of statistical techniques to analyze the IAT, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
